added.title: Excalibear
added.description: On the Bears' visit to a medieval vegetable-village, Grizz starts to believe that he's the rightful king.

added.title: Meat House
added.description: The Bears and their new friend Squatter Otter attempt to live in mysterious house made of meat.

added.title: Pirate Parrot Polly
added.description: On their quest for hidden treasure, the Bears team up with Polly the Parrot Pirate.

added.title: Baby Bear Genius
added.description: Ice Bear receives an invitation to attend a prestigious school for baby geniuses… but Grizz and Panda do not.

added.title: Bug City Sleuths
added.description: To survive in a city inhabited by bugs, the Bears become noir-style detectives.

added.title: The Tree Stooges Save Christmas Part 1
added.description: The kids accidentally destroy Chef's decorated Christmas tree. Scared this means they've ruined his Christmas, they go on an epic mission to replace his holiday treasures.

added.title: The Tree Stooges Save Christmas Part 2
added.description: The kids accidentally destroy Chef's decorated Christmas tree. Scared this means they've ruined his Christmas, they go on an epic mission to replace his holiday treasures.

added.title: Me, My Elf, and I
added.description: Duncan tricks Chef into taking the class to the North Pole in order to remove his name from the naughty list.

added.title: Snow Way Out
added.description: Owen wants everyone to love his new snowsuit and envy him, but it's just not working out that way.

added.title: Merry Christmas
added.description: When the Rustbucket's A/C goes on the fritz in the middle of the desert, Ben, Max and Gwen take refuge at Holiday Village, an over the top Christmas theme park that seems to appear out of nowhere. The place is run by an evil entity known as Mr. Jingles, who takes Max prisoner because he believes Max is Santa! It's up to Ben and Gwen to free Max and break the spell Mr. Jingles has cast on Holiday Village, freeing others who've been trapped their for years and releasing the theme park.

added.title: Benwolf
added.description: In New Mexico, Max stops to visit an old friend, who's a Navajo Chief. Suddenly, a powerful storm comes out of nowhere. And behind bolts of purple lightning, a Navajo werewolf appears. As Ben battles the werewolf, he appears to be bitten and turns into Benwolf.

added.title: Game Over
added.description: When Ben, as Upgrade, and Gwen get zapped into a Sumo Slammers video game, Ben soon has to deal with Gwen's superior gaming skills, while he also tries to impress his video icon in the game.

added.title: Monster Weather
added.description: Max takes the kids to a drought stricken Chicago to see his favorite golden oldie band perform at a huge music festival. Once there, our heroes cross paths with a deranged weatherman.

added.title: Super Alien Hero Buddy Adventures
added.description: Ben discovers his alien heroes have been ripped off by a lame cartoon and he is not happy. So he sets out to make things right.

added.title: Looneyburg Lights
added.description: The Looney Builders prepare to host a big holiday lights festival in Looneyburg Park when an unexpected snowstorm prevents Looneyburgers from attending.

added.title: Blast Off
added.description: When Marvin the Martian crash lands in Looneyburg, he's in a hurry to leave and hires The Looney Builders to build him a spaceship.

added.title: Bedtime Routine
added.description: Jessica wants to be a big kid and get ready for bed all on her own, but she can't remember everything in her routine.

added.title: Glow Toy
added.description: When Jessica can't get a new toy to work, she learns a new way to appreciate it.

added.title: The Escaping Cows of Sunny Field Farm/Measure For Measure
added.description: Zee's new drone accidentally doubles as a cow caller, and the cows keep leaving the farm to go see it. But how?/Marwyn attempts to make Pretty Big City's largest cookie, but to do so, he'll need a lot of help.

added.title: Special Delivery/Super Duper Sled Slide
added.description: The Martians want to help LLoyd deliver packages, but keep breaking them when they drop them from up high./MacBarm and Zee built a slide that sends people all the way across the farm… which means people spend more time walking than sliding.

added.title: Bear Hibernation
added.description: Blippi wonders how do bears prepare for hibernation?

added.title: Snowy Excavator Song
added.description: A special animated music video episode to the tune of Blippi's new "Snowy Excavator" Song.

added.title: Christmas Scavenger Hunt
added.description: Blippi wonders what is the best part about Christmas?

added.title: Blippi Saves Christmas
added.description: Blippi wonders how does Santa know where we live?

added.title: Penguins
added.description: Blippi wonders can penguins fly?

added.title: O'Little Tree
added.description: Mei shows Ella and Rishi the magic of Christmas - by growing an adorable Christmas tree in the middle of the farm.

added.title: The Penguin Dance
added.description: Rico the penguin is visiting Lellobee city farm… and he's travelled all the way from the North pole!

added.title: The Christmas Parade
added.description: Mei, Ella, Rishi get the farm decorated for the holidayss and do various christmassy activities

added.title: Holiday Party
added.description: "Lighting up the farm for a big 'festive' celebration Lots of lights around the farm and decorations from different cultures"

added.title: Chinese New Year
added.description: The farm is decorated for Chinese New Year. A party is taking place!

added.title: The Big Kid Playground
added.description: Jessica goes in the big kid part of the playground for the first time, and befriends Stanleigh.

added.title: Grocery Store Friend
added.description: While helping Duane at the supermarket, Jessica meets a new friend and has trouble staying focused on her responsibilities.

added.title: Pull Together/Lift Up and Lift Off
added.description: Ranger Nat is stuck at the bottom of the crevice, but the problem grows when Mecha Abby also gets stuck./Zee is ready to launch his rocket into space, but when the launchpad breaks, the rocket is launched into the farm instead.

added.title: That Ol' Time Rock Rolls!/Make Like a Banana and Split
added.description: When Big Old Boulder rolls down the hill towards the museum, Berta needs the Mechas help to keep it stable./It's Food Day in Pretty Big City, but the Mechas need to help when the banana atop the banana split statue is not split!
